From Blaine Gardner Subject Re MOTORCYCLE DETAILING TIP In article MBEAVING writes Don't you just hate when the speedo and tach on your bike start to cloud over from all that nasty sunshine The detailing tip of the week is to use rubbing Moisten a rag apply some rubbing compound and work into the translucent previously transparent After a few minutes of working on the plastic face the dial or plastic face will be clear once Will not work for A couple of other Make a habit of parking the bike so that instruments are facing away from the Meguiar's Mirror Glaze Plastic Polish Plastic Cue canned product plug Linda Roise writes OK for a novice question is there anything that will clean a face shield and also remove abrasions so that one can see through it better What you want are Meguiar's Mirror Glaze Plastic Polish and Plastic They are very mild abrasives meant to remove scratches from For fine scratches just use the Polish for bigger ones start with the Cleaner and finish with the The stuff is bucks per bottle at most auto or motorcycle parts Don't choke over the price too much since both bottles will probably last you The stuff works great on plastic watch crystals and compact discs Blaine Gardner Evans Sutherland